biography.text:
Long before GRAMMY® nods, global chart-toppers, and billions of streams, Swedish House Mafia Co-Founder Steve Angello found his passion in Sweden. He co-founded Size Records in 2003 and, alongside Axwell in Supermode, struck gold with "Tell Me Why." In 2008, Swedish House Mafia emerged, with back-to-back GRAMMY® nods for "Best Dance Recording" for hits like "Save the World" and "Don't You Worry Child."

They sold out iconic venues and rocked Coachella, Ultra Music Festival, and more. Steve also shone as a solo powerhouse, featuring on DJ Mag's "Top 100 DJs" list for 14 years and earning two DJ Awards. His remixes span Justin Timberlake, Coldplay, Depeche Mode, Fergie, and Moby.

Following his debut album "Wild Youth," 2018's "Human" showcased his evolution, collaborating with Bishop T.D. Jakes, Pusha T, Barns Courtney, and more. In 2021, Swedish House Mafia's triumphant return with "Paradise Again" hit #1 on Billboard's Dance/Electronic and UK Dance Albums charts, leading to a colossal world tour.

Steve Angello continues pushing boundaries, promising more music and transformative experiences in 2024.
